results.name: Array T(n,k) read by antidiagonals: T(n,k) is the number of [n,k]-triangulations in the plane that have reflection symmetry, n >= 0, k >= 0.
comment: "A closed bounded region in the plane divided into triangular regions with k+3 vertices on the boundary and n internal vertices is said to be a triangular map of type [n,k]." It is a [n,k]-triangulation if there are no multiple edges.
"... may be evaluated from the results given by Brown."
reference: C. F. Earl and L. J. March, Architectural applications of graph theory, pp. 327-355 of R. J. Wilson and L. W. Beineke, editors, Applications of Graph Theory. Academic Press, NY, 1979.
